node.title: Victoria records 21,997 cases, six deaths and 631 hospitalisations
node.alt: A surgeon concentrating during an operation at St Vincent's Hospital
node.description: The hospitalisations are the highest in the state since November 6, and include 51 patients in ICU, with 22 people on ventilators.
node.content:
["The number of patients with COVID-19 in Victorian hospitals has leapt to 631, as the state records 21,997\u00a0new cases and six\u00a0further deaths.", "The hospitalisations are the highest in the state since November 6, and include 51\u00a0patients in ICU, with 22\u00a0people on ventilators.", "A further 49\u00a0patients whose infections are no longer active are still receiving care in ICU.", "The rise in infections marks a new record for the state and was\u00a0 detected from 64,861 test results, taking the test positivity rate to 34 per cent.", "There are now 61,120\u00a0active cases in Victoria and 737\u00a0people have died in the current outbreak.", "As of today, the Victorian government has put a freeze on all but the most-urgent elective surgeries, as staff infections and rising cases overwhelm the healthcare system.", "", "
New website launched to track down rapid antigen tests
"]
